	(text "This board schematic is a minimum version of the E1k Dev Kit v3 schematic\n\nE1k Page 2 - Power Input - Omitted\n	Power input selection switch, and regulators for 3V3 and 5V level shifters removed.\n	This board is powered entirely off of 1.8V (Equivalent to the 1V8_DCDC net in the E1k schematic).\n\nE1k Page 3 & 4 - E1 IO & E1 Power - Replicated in Page 2 - SoM\n	All ARD_* nets omitted\n	Shunt Resistors and signals omitted.\n	Boot mode and JTAG ctrl switches omitted, but signals broken out. Must be set, and broken out on carrier board.\n	Programming header omitted but signals broken out. Must be broken out on carrier board.\n\nE1k Page 5, 6, & 7 - Debug, Debug Power, & Debug Jumpers - Omitted\n	Replicated in programmer board.\n	All signals routed to RP2040 broken out. Must be broken out on carrier board.\n\nE1k Page 8 - Current Measurement - Omitted\n	U23 and U25 (VDDIO and 0V55) Shunt resistors removed and so cannot be used.\n	U9 and U24 (SYS and 1V8) may be placed on carrier board. I2C lines broken out to programmer.\n\nE1k Page 9, 10, & 11 - Arduino Power, UNO Headers, & MKR Headers - Omitted\n	This board is entirely 1.8V. Any level shifters must be placed on carrier board.\n\nE1k Page 12 - User IO - Partially replicated in Page 5 - Connectors\n	All 12 GPIO banks broken out.\n	Bank 2 (QSPI Flash), should be unused on carrier board.\n	Bank 3 pins 4 and 5 are E1 UART and should be broken out on carrier board.\n	Bank 4 pins 4 and 5 are MSP430 UART and should be unused on carrier board.\n	User I/O switches and LED omitted. Any user I/O must be on carrier board.\n\nE1k Page 13 - QSPI NVM - Replicated Verbatim in Page 4 - QSPI Flash\n	Bank 2 routed to QSPI Flash (MRAM).\n\nE1k Page 14 - Housekeeping - Replicated in Page 3 - Housekeeping\n	Using QFN package variant of MSP430 MCU used in E1k schematic.\n	Pinout identical to E1k schematic.\n"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
